

Task 2:

T2_4.fd.m is used for automatic matching for both FD and HG sets.

T2.2.matching_manual.m is used to do manual matching.



Task 4:

First, compile and run T4.2.hough.m to know positions of crossing lines and vanishing points.

Then use T4.2.VPs_manual.m to draw vanishing poins and the horizon based on prvious observations in T4.2.hough.m.

T4.2.add_epp.m is used to add epipoles which are outside the image.

Task 5:

To start with, you need to have your photos undistorted. Then feed undistorted pictures to T5.1.stereo_rect.m, and you will get stereo rectified photos.
